[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests/Records/Drawing/DrawingPropertiesPanel.cs:154 por @Copilot]: ChangeFeaturePermission returns the previous permission level; setting this to IsAllowed without capturing the return value makes it impossible to restore the original state later (and the test currently hard-resets to IsDenied). Capture the previous value so the test can restore whatever was configured before it ran.
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests/Records/Drawing/DrawingPropertiesPanel.cs:199 por @Copilot]: The cleanup at the end of the test currently forces CanViewSharingHistory to IsDenied, which may not match the previous configured value for this user group. Restore the previously captured permission level instead.
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests/Records/Drawing/DrawingPropertiesPanel.cs:154 por @Copilot]: Feature permissions are shared test state; if any assertion fails before the end of the method, the permission will remain modified and can cascade failures into later tests. Wrap the test body in a try/finally (or restore in CustomTestCleanupAsync) so the original permission is always restored (see docs/ai/INTEGRATION_TEST_CONVENTIONS.md §9).
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests/_Pages/Pages/DrawingFDEF.cs:241 por @Copilot]: The drawing detail overlay root element is always present in the DOM and is shown/hidden via the `[hidden]` attribute (see drawing-detail-overlay.component.html). Using `.Exists()` against `.drawing-detail-overlay` can report true even when the overlay is not actually visible. Scope the overlay to `:not([hidden])` (or equivalent XPath `not(@hidden)`) so IsShown() and child locators only succeed when the overlay is open.
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests/Records/Drawing/DrawingPropertiesPanel.cs:168 por @Copilot]: `_originalSharingHistoryPermission` is assigned but never used. In this test project `TreatWarningsAsErrors` is enabled (`Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests.csproj:11`), so this will fail the build as an unused-variable warning.

Either remove the assignment (if cleanup is the intended reset path), or actually use the returned value to restore the prior permission in `finally`/`CustomTestCleanupAsync`.
[Comentario en Core/Tests/ProjectSight.Tests.ParallelBrowserTests/Records/Drawing/DrawingPropertiesPanel.cs:35 por @Copilot]: Cleanup restores CanViewSharingHistory to PermissionLevel.IsDenied based on TestContext.TestName. That assumes the default permission is always denied and also risks leaking the permission change if the test is renamed or if other tests in this class later toggle the same permission. Prefer tracking the previous permission level when you change it, and restoring it unconditionally in cleanup when it was modified.
